## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="15157-102">という名前の XML スキーマ要素定義`xsi:choice`インスタンス内の 1 つだけの子を含むことのできる複雑な要素を定義するために使用 (maxoccurs = 1)。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-102">The XML schema element definition named `xsi:choice` is used to define a complex element that can contain only one child in an instance (maxoccurs = 1).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15157-103">いくつかの名前のいずれかのことができます、その子には、いくつかの種類のいずれかを指定できます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-103">That child can be one of several types, and it can have one of several names.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15157-104">それぞれの名前は、特定の種類に関連付けただし、いくつかの名前と同じ型に関連付けることができます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-104">Each name is associated with a specific type; however, several names can be associated with the same type.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15157-105">このため、このような要素のインスタンスでは異なります。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-105">Because of this, an instance of such an element is indistinct.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15157-106">たとえば、このような不明瞭という名前の要素を定義する次のスキーマ フラグメント`MyChoice`します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-106">For example, consider the following schema fragment that defines such an indistinct element named `MyChoice`.</span></span>  
  
```  
<xsd:complexType name="MyChoice">  
 <xsd:sequence>  
 <xsd:choice minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1">  
 <xsd:element minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="1" name="ChoiceOne" type="xsd:string" />  
 <xsd:element minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="1" name="ChoiceTwo" type="xsd:string" />  
 </xsd:choice>  
 </xsd:sequence>  
</xsd:complexType>  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="15157-107"><xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute>メンバーの各インスタンスに特殊な列挙値を割り当てることができます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-107">The <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute> allows you to assign a special enumeration value to each instance of the member.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15157-108">必要がありますか、列挙、自分で作成またはによって生成されることができますが、 [XML スキーマ定義ツール (Xsd.exe)](~/docs/standard/serialization/xml-schema-definition-tool-xsd-exe.md)します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-108">You must either create the enumeration yourself or it can be generated by the [XML Schema Definition Tool (Xsd.exe)](~/docs/standard/serialization/xml-schema-definition-tool-xsd-exe.md).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15157-109">次の c# コード表示方法、<xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute>に適用される、 `Item` ; フィールド、<xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute.MemberName%2A>プロパティは、さらに、選択肢を検出するために使用される列挙体を含むフィールドを識別します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-109">The following C# code shows how the <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute> is applied to an `Item` field; the <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute.MemberName%2A> property identifies the field that contains the enumeration that is further used to detect the choice.</span></span>  
  
```  
public class Choices{  
 [XmlChoiceIdentifier("ItemType")]  
 [XmlChoiceIdentifier("ChoiceOne")]  
 [XmlChoiceIdentifier("ChoiceTwo")]  
 public string MyChoice;  
  
 // Do not serialize this next field:  
 [XmlIgnore]  
 public ItemChoiceType ItemType;  
}  
// Do not include this enumeration in the XML schema.  
[XmlType(IncludeInSchema = false)]  
public enum ItemChoiceType{  
 ChoiceOne,  
 ChoiceTwo,  
}  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="15157-110">このコードが、シリアル化し、設定してこのクラスを逆シリアル化、`ItemType`フィールドを適切な列挙体。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-110">When this code is in place, you can serialize and deserialize this class by setting the `ItemType` field to an appropriate enumeration.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15157-111">たとえば、シリアル化するため、`Choice`次のようにクラスを c# コードです。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-111">For example, to serialize the `Choice` class, the C# code resembles the following.</span></span>  
  
```  
Choices mc = new Choices();  
mc.MyChoice = "Item Choice One";  
mc.ItemType = ItemChoiceType.ChoiceOne;  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="15157-112">逆シリアル化するときに、c# コードは、次のようになります。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-112">When deserializing, the C# code resembles the following:</span></span>  
  
```  
MyChoice mc = (MyChoice) myXmlSerializer.Deserialize(myReader);  
if(mc.ItemType == ItemChoiceType.ChoiceOne)  
 {  
     // Handle choice one.  
 }  
if(mc.ItemType == ItemChoiceType.ChoiceTwo)  
 {  
     // Handle choice two.  
 }  
if(mc.ItemType != null)  
 {  
     throw CreateUnknownTypeException(mc.Item);  
 }  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="15157-113">2 番目のシナリオがあるときに、<xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute>使用されます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-113">There is a second scenario when the <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute> is used.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15157-114">次のスキーマでは、メンバーは、項目の配列を返すフィールド (maxOccurs ="unbounded")。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-114">In the following schema, the member is a field that returns an array of items (maxOccurs="unbounded").</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15157-115">配列は、最初の任意のオブジェクトを含めることができます ("D-、-t-a")、および 2 つ目の選択肢 ("MoreData") のです。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-115">The array can contain objects of the first choice ("D-a-t-a"), and of the second choice ("MoreData").</span></span>  
  
```  
<xsd:complexType name="MyChoice">  
 <xsd:sequence>  
 <xsd:choice minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">  
 <xsd:element minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="1" name="D-a-t-a" type="xsd:string" />  
 <xsd:element minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="1" name="MoreData" type="xsd:string" />  
 </xsd:choice>  
 </xsd:sequence>  
</xsd:complexType>  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="15157-116">結果として得られるクラスは、このフィールドを使用して項目の配列を返します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-116">The resulting class then uses a field to return an array of items.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15157-117">対応する、配列の各項目の`ItemChoiceType`でも列挙型を確認する必要があります。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-117">For each item in the array, a corresponding `ItemChoiceType` enumeration must also be found.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15157-118">一致する列挙体は、によって返される配列内に含まれる、`ItemsElementName`フィールド。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-118">The matching enumerations are contained in the array returned by the `ItemsElementName` field.</span></span>  
  
```  
public class MyChoice {  
 [System.Xml.Serialization.XmlElementAttribute("D-a-t-a", typeof(string), IsNullable=false)]  
 [System.Xml.Serialization.XmlElementAttribute("MoreData", typeof(string), IsNullable=false)]  
 [System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute("ItemsElementName")]  
 public string[] Items;  
 [System.Xml.Serialization.XmlElementAttribute(IsNullable=false)]  
 [System.Xml.Serialization.XmlIgnoreAttribute()]  
 public ItemsChoiceType[] ItemsElementName;  
}  
[System.Xml.Serialization.XmlTypeAttribute(IncludeInSchema=false)]  
public enum ItemsChoiceType {  
 [System.Xml.Serialization.XmlEnumAttribute("D-a-t-a")]  
 Data,  
 MoreData,  
}  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="15157-119">選択肢の範囲を含むオブジェクトを逆シリアル化するときに、制御構造を使用して (if など... then... else 構造の) 特定の値を逆シリアル化する方法を決定します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-119">When deserializing an object that includes a range of choices, use a control structure (such as an if...then...else structure) to determine how to deserialize a particular value.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15157-120">制御構造体で列挙値を確認し、それに応じて値を逆シリアル化します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-120">In the control structure, check the enumeration value and deserialize the value accordingly.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="15157-121">次の例では、という名前のクラスをシリアル化`Choices`2 つのフィールドを含む`MyChoice`と`ManyChoices`します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-121">The following example serializes a class named `Choices` that includes two fields, `MyChoice` and `ManyChoices`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15157-122"><xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute>を指定する各フィールドに適用される (を通じて、<xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute.MemberName%2A>プロパティ) を取得または設定の列挙体メンバーの値を検出する別のクラスのメンバー。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-122">The <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute> is applied to each field that specifies (through the <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlChoiceIdentifierAttribute.MemberName%2A> property) another class member that gets or sets an enumeration that detects the member value.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15157-123">`MyChoice`フィールドにある、対応する列挙型メンバーの 1 つの値に設定できます、`EnumType`フィールド。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-123">The `MyChoice` field can be set to a single value, with a corresponding enumeration member found in the `EnumType` field.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15157-124">`ManyChoices`フィールドはオブジェクトの配列を返します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-124">The `ManyChoices` field returns an array of objects.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15157-125">`ChoiceArray`フィールドが列挙値の配列を返します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-125">The `ChoiceArray` field returns an array of enumeration values.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15157-126">配列のメンバーごとに、`ManyChoices`フィールドに、対応するメンバーは、によって返される配列で見つかりましたが、`ChoiceArray`フィールド。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15157-126">For each array member in the `ManyChoices` field, a corresponding member is found in the array returned by the `ChoiceArray` field.</span></span>  
  
